# Hard Prohibitions — Never Do These

- Do NOT hardcode paths. All paths from config.yaml.
- Do NOT use subprocess to call OpenSim CLI. Use Python API only.
- Do NOT use plt.show() in src/. Return Figure objects.
- Do NOT put logic in notebooks that is not also in src/.
- Do NOT use threading for parallelism. Use multiprocessing only.
- Do NOT use lambdas or closures as multiprocessing worker functions.
- Do NOT write metadata.json directly. Always use dataset_io.save_metadata() (atomic write).
- Do NOT import opensim at module top-level.
- Do NOT save activations as float64. Always cast to float32.
- Do NOT hardcode N_muscles. Derive from len(muscle_names).
- Do NOT hardcode fps. Derive from config['output']['output_fps'].
- Do NOT use print() in src/ or scripts/. Use logging.
